{"word":"καυχάομαι","slug":"καυχάομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ϰαυχάομαι</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ cp.\">cp.</a> <el>ϰαύχη</el> ‘boast’] ‘have or express pride in being intimately associated or involved with’ some <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pers.\">pers.</a>, thing, or circumstance, <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ oft.\">oft.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:ἐν\">ἐν</a></el> <b>boast <a href='B:520 2:17'>Ro 2:17</a>, <a href='B:520 2:23'>23</a>; <a href='B:520 5:2'>5:2f</a>; <a href='B:530 1:31'>1 Cor 1:31</a></b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ oft.\">oft.</a> in the Pauline corpus. Frequently the rationale or basis for boasting is implied in the context <b><a href='B:530 1:29'>1 Cor 1:29</a>; <a href='B:530 4:7'>4:7</a>; <a href='B:540 10:8'>2 Cor 10:8</a>; <a href='B:540 11:16'>11:16</a>, <a href='B:540 11:18'>18</a>; <a href='B:540 12:1'>12:1</a>; <a href='B:560 2:9'>Eph 2:9</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:καυτηριάζω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:καύχημα\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}